{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Ksxxz3tAm2nHLLpkzgDgTJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need to compile the compliance audit findings. Let me analyze what I've found:\n\n**RBAC:**\n1. ✅ A dedicated ServiceAccount `spark-pi` exists (not using `default` SA)\n2. ✅ A Role `spark-pi-role` is defined with namespace-scoped permissions only\n3. ✅ A RoleBinding `spark-pi-role-binding` binds the role to the `spark-pi` SA\n4. ⚠️ The Role grants broad verbs (create, get, list, watch, delete, update, patch) on services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims, and pods — includes `delete` and `patch` which are powerful verbs\n5. ✅ No ClusterRole or ClusterRoleBinding is used — namespace-scoped only\n\n**Resource Limits:**\nAll three components (spark-master, spark-worker, and spark-pi job) have consistent resource limits set at 500m CPU and 1Gi memory, with requests at 200m CPU and 512Mi memory.\n\n**Image Provenance:**\nNow I'm checking the container image sources.\n\nThe manifests use `apache/spark:3.5.3` with a specific version tag rather than `latest`, which is good, but there's no digest pinning — the tag itself could theoretically be reassigned. The `imagePullPolicy` is set to `IfNotPresent`, so if the tag gets updated, the cached image won't be re-pulled, which could cause inconsistencies.\n\n**Security Context:**\nAll pod security contexts are empty across both deployments and the job, missing critical hardening like `runAsNonRoot`, explicit `runAsUser`, `readOnlyRootFilesystem`, `allowPrivilegeEscalation: false`, and capability dropping.\n\n**Network Policies:**\nNo NetworkPolicy resources exist in the namespace, meaning all pods can communicate freely with each other and across namespaces without restriction.\n\nThe spark-pi job completed successfully, and I'm now organizing these findings into a structured compliance report with sections for RBAC, resource limits, image provenance, and security context to save as a ConfigMap.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1742,"cache_read_input_tokens":31601,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1742},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"da539591-330f-4019-9778-b0bae17b0f86","uuid":"b26ce1ff-0155-4ec3-b272-366a0204a1cb","request_id":"req_011Cc6kTkX6SsnJSt4LoDiqB"}
